## SEO Activity Without a Strategy Is Expensive Guesswork

Most Reading businesses doing SEO are in the same position: content is being published, technical issues are being fixed, but the results don't reflect the investment. Rankings are patchy. Traffic growth has plateaued. Nobody is sure whether to push harder on content, backlinks, technical improvements, or local signals.

The missing piece is almost always strategy — a documented, prioritised plan that connects specific SEO activities to specific business outcomes, and defines the sequence that builds compound growth rather than isolated wins.

Without a strategy, SEO budget gets allocated to whichever activity seems most urgent rather than whichever will deliver the highest return. With one, every piece of content, every technical fix, and every optimisation serves a defined architecture.

